data.title: Shannon RFC – Rugby
data.text:
Josh Costello spearheaded Shannon’s push for survival in 1A, as they produced an empathic second half performance to edge Highfield in the Munster Derby.

Continue reading “Shannon Edge Munster Derby For 1A Survival” →

Four finals are down for decision today in the AIL, with plenty of high’s and low’s expected as for some it will be a day of jubilitation.

Continue reading “AIL Preview: Men’s Divisional Finals” →

In a high exciting game in the capital, Shannon picked up a much needed win over Lansdowne, which moves them up to seventh place ahead of the Christmas Break.

Continue reading “AIL Roundup: Division 1A Week 9 Refixed” →

Just one refixed tie in 1A this weekend, where Lansdowne host Shannon in what is very much a must win game for both teams.

Continue reading “AIL Preview: Division 1A Week 9 Refixed” →

The most successful club in the history of the AIL return to the top division this weekend, where they will face last year’s runners up, Terenure College.

Continue reading “Shannon RFC eager to impress and use youth ahead of return to Division 1A.” →

With the return of the All Ireland League this weekend The Rugby Show is back on FinalWhistle.ie as Shannon’s Director of Rugby Pat Browne and Leinster & Wicklow full back Ella Roberts join Luke Delaney at 8pm this evening.

Continue reading “Pat Brown & Ella Roberts – S 2 Ep 1” →

Shannon will return to top tier of the AIL following a deserved 30-15 victory over Naas at Coonagh on Saturday afternoon.

Continue reading “1B Final – Shannon return to the top” →
